<p>Gruber wrote <a href="https://daringfireball.net/2025/03/something_is_rotten_in_the_state_of_cupertino" target="_blank">Daring Fireball Something Is Rotten in the State of Cupertino</a>.</p>
<p>I am not going to rewrite the article for you. Go read it.</p>
<p>This is a quote from the article.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>When mediocrity, excuses, and bullshit take root, they take over. A culture of excellence, accountability, and integrity cannot abide the acceptance of any of those things, and will quickly collapse upon itself with the acceptance of all three.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Reminded me of what Guy Kawasaki called “bozosity.” I think Apple is afflicted with that.</p>
